        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>painters by technique, implement, or material employed [300025143], painters (artists) [300025136], artists by medium or work type [300386777], artists (visual artists) [300025103], people in the visual arts [300025101], people in the visual arts and related occupations [300239109], people in the arts [300168455], people in the arts and related occupations [300168331], people in the humanities [300025485], people by occupation [300024980], people (agents) [300024979], People (hierarchy name) [300024978], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Artists or craftsmen who paint directly on fabric with the goal of decorating drapery, banners, or another textile. The term does not refer to artists who create oil paintings or paintings in another media on canvas or another fabric, where the goal is to create a scene or other work of art that will be displayed in a frame or hung on a wall.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046795/Adams Bentley, Acrylic and Fabric Painter's Reference Book (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046796/Kanzinger, Fabric Painting Resources (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Artistas o artesanos que pintan directamente sobre tela con el fin de de obtener paños decorados, banderas u otros textiles. El término no se refiere a artistas que crean pinturas al óleo o pinturas con otras técnicas sobre tela u otros textiles, donde el fin consiste en crear escenas u otras obras que serán exihibidas con marco o colgadas sobre una pared.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kunstenaars of ambachtslieden die rechtstreeks op weefsel schilderen, voor het decoreren van draperieën, vaandels of ander textiel. De term verwijst niet naar kunstenaars die in olieverf of een ander medium op linnen of een andere stof schilderen, met als het doel het creëren van een tafereel of ander kunstwerk dat wordt ingelijst en tentoongesteld of aan de muur wordt gehangen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
